{"lemma":"شاحِبَةٍ","slug":"شاحِبَةٍ","root":"ش.ح.ب","root_slug":"ش-ح-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ح-ب","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21813"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%AD%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"pale"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"emaciated, haggard"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"dim"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"dull (color)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of شَحَبَ (šaḥaba, “to be pale”), شَحُبَ (šaḥuba, “(same)”), and passive verb شُحِبَ (šuḥiba, “(same)”)."},"ipa":["/ʃaː.ħib/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21813","headword_ar":"شَاحِبٌ","root":"$Hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having his colour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complexion, altered"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the worse, wan,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"haggard"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAHibu All~awoni","text_ar":"شَاحِبُ اللَّوْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in consequence of disease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"travel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA: [see 1:]) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emaciated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lean;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, KL;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aHibN","text_ar":"شَحِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (KL.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA taloqaY Almuw^omina A_il~aA","text_ar":"لَا تَلْقَى المُوْمِنَ اـِلَّا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAHibFA","text_ar":"شَاحِبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou wilt not find the believer otherwise than wan,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"haggard;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emaciated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lean"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uHuwb","text_ar":"شُحُوب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is one of the effects of fear, and of paucity of food, and of little enjoying of plentifulness and pleasantness or easiness, and softness or delicacy, of life. (TA.) ―         -b2-  It is also applied as an epithet to a sword, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Altered in its colour by blood that has dried upon it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"used in this sense by the poet Taäbbata-sharrà. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}